"{\"uid\": \"abc.net.au-news-2024-07-31-paris-2024-olympic-games-kaylee-mckeown-100m-backstroke-104162712\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Personalise the news and  stay in the know  Emergency  Backstory  Newsletters  \\u4e2d\\u6587\\u65b0\\u95fb  BERITA BAHASA INDONESIA  TOK PISIN  Find any issues using dark mode?Please let us know  Sport  analysis  Topic:Olympic Games  Kaylee McKeown is an Olympic gold medallist again.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 261, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 92, \"end\": 108, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesian_language\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"BAHASA INDONESIA\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 211, \"end\": 225, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kaylee McKeown\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Getty Images: Sarah Stier)  There can not be too many swimmers as up for a scrap as Kaylee McKeown.\", \"from\": 261, \"to\": 361, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 276, \"end\": 281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Jane_Smith\", \"score\": 0.5840334627634629, \"rank\": 0.7122198439535354, \"text\": \"Sarah\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Jane_Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Jane_Smith\"}, {\"begin\": 346, \"end\": 360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kaylee McKeown\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The world's most dominant backstroke swimmer, holder of six individual titles at world and Olympic level, owner of two long-course world records.\", \"from\": 363, \"to\": 508, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And now,back-to-back Olympic champion in the 100 metres.\", \"from\": 510, \"to\": 566, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It feels surreal to be honest with you,\\\" McKeown said.\", \"from\": 568, \"to\": 623, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I wasn't sure if I'd be any good there tonight.\", \"from\": 625, \"to\": 673, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I did not put expectations on myself.\", \"from\": 674, \"to\": 711, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I was going to get out and enjoy the atmosphere, and that's the best you can do for yourself.\\\"\", \"from\": 712, \"to\": 806, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is not that McKeown won that was most impressive.\", \"from\": 808, \"to\": 860, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was that she had the gauntlet thrown down in front of her by a former champion and a world record ripped away.\", \"from\": 862, \"to\": 975, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And she did not even blink.\", \"from\": 977, \"to\": 1004, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"McKeown was all business when she came out of the tunnel, marching to her block with eyes only on the prize at stake.\", \"from\": 1006, \"to\": 1123, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The nerves were definitely there,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 1125, \"to\": 1170, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But I reminded myself that it's a pool in a different venue, and I train every single day of my life.\", \"from\": 1172, \"to\": 1274, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Regan Smith was more flamboyant with her entry, taking the time to enjoy her moment, waving her arms and then slowly undressing at her chair.\", \"from\": 1276, \"to\": 1417, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1276, \"end\": 1287, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.231257919324237e-30, \"text\": \"Regan Smith\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Keeping everyone waiting.\", \"from\": 1419, \"to\": 1444, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Games, within games, letting those nerves build in her waiting adversaries.\", \"from\": 1445, \"to\": 1520, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With French women in the two outside lanes, the swimmers inside could have been lulled into the false security that they were anonymous to the majority of the crowd.\", \"from\": 1522, \"to\": 1687, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1527, \"end\": 1533, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999564013496907, \"rank\": 4.040929640513672e-05, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the masses of Americans present made sure there was no doubt the interest was in the centre of the pool.\", \"from\": 1689, \"to\": 1797, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And McKeown knew.\", \"from\": 1799, \"to\": 1816, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She knew where the threats were and knew exactly how she'd respond to them.\", \"from\": 1817, \"to\": 1892, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Want more?Here's the full list of all our Olympics stories  Bouncing on her toes before being allowed into the water, McKeown wasted no time in getting into her work once the buzzer went and the crowd roared.\", \"from\": 1894, \"to\": 2102, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She went out hard, holding the line along with the Americans to her right, Smith and Katharine Berkoff.\", \"from\": 2104, \"to\": 2207, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2189, \"end\": 2206, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katharine_Berkoff\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katharine Berkoff\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katharine_Berkoff\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katharine_Berkoff\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was Canadian Kylie Masse in lane two who leaped out to turn first though, dead level with Smith, McKeown fourth behind Berkoff.\", \"from\": 2209, \"to\": 2339, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2216, \"end\": 2224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.9999843797474001, \"rank\": 1.5619950670042153e-05, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kaylee McKeown had to come from behind at the turn to rein in Regan Smith.\", \"from\": 2341, \"to\": 2415, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2341, \"end\": 2355, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kaylee McKeown\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\"}, {\"begin\": 2403, \"end\": 2414, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.231257919324237e-30, \"text\": \"Regan Smith\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Getty Images: Maddie Meyer)  In the second 50m though, McKeown turned it on, drawn through by Masse, Berkoff and Smith, the four in a line through 75m with the race anyone's to win.\", \"from\": 2415, \"to\": 2597, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2430, \"end\": 2436, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maddie_Coleman\", \"score\": 0.999999488702673, \"rank\": 5.112977826299447e-07, \"text\": \"Maddie\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maddie_Coleman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maddie_Coleman\"}, {\"begin\": 2437, \"end\": 2442, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephenie_Meyer\", \"score\": 0.9999999998121893, \"rank\": 1.240698242372308e-10, \"text\": \"Meyer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephenie_Meyer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephenie_Meyer\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And that's where the racer comes in.\", \"from\": 2599, \"to\": 2635, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's where that little bit of a chip on the shoulder comes into play, that dogged unwillingness to be beaten when it really counts.\", \"from\": 2637, \"to\": 2770, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I knew it was going to come down to the last five metres,\\\" McKeown said.\", \"from\": 2772, \"to\": 2845, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are both extremely good athletes, and both extremely good trainers, so it's just who feels better on the day, and she pushed me the whole way through.\", \"from\": 2847, \"to\": 3001, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You wait for the race and finish it, and I can not even remember it now.\\\"\", \"from\": 3003, \"to\": 3077, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Timing is everything in sport.\", \"from\": 3079, \"to\": 3109, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Get it right and everything follows how it's meant to.\", \"from\": 3110, \"to\": 3164, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"McKeown was frustrated at trials for missing her world record by less than a tenth of a second.\", \"from\": 3166, \"to\": 3261, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Smith meanwhile, was confident that breaking McKeown's world record by a whopping 0.2 seconds in Indianapolis was \\\"part of the plan\\\".\", \"from\": 3263, \"to\": 3396, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3360, \"end\": 3372, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis\", \"score\": 0.9999089272251597, \"rank\": 7.117942925580048e-05, \"text\": \"Indianapolis\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Timing matters.\", \"from\": 3398, \"to\": 3413, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here, McKeown swam the exact same time of her previous world record, 57.33, enough to claim the Olympic record and a fourth Olympic gold medal.\", \"from\": 3415, \"to\": 3558, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Smith was second just 0.33 seconds behind, Berkoff a further 0.32 behind her to round out the podium.\", \"from\": 3560, \"to\": 3661, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kaylee McKeown lets it all out after winning 100m backstroke gold.\", \"from\": 3663, \"to\": 3729, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3663, \"end\": 3677, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kaylee McKeown\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Reuters: Grace Hollars)  McKeown's reaction was typical of that racer, up on the lane rope, a punch of the air, before slapping the water with a burst of what looked a touch like relief.\", \"from\": 3729, \"to\": 3916, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3730, \"end\": 3737, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.298131299506442e-19, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 3739, \"end\": 3744, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grace_Adler\", \"score\": 0.9998607457398216, \"rank\": 0.00013836585944992385, \"text\": \"Grace\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grace_Adler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grace_Adler\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Someone had come for her crown, and despite being put under enormous pressure, she saw them off.\", \"from\": 3918, \"to\": 4014, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With four gold medals, McKeown is now one of Australia's most decorated Olympians.\", \"from\": 4016, \"to\": 4098, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4061, \"end\": 4070, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.999999995451617, \"rank\": 3.0371803434256807e-09, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ABC Sport Daily is your daily sports conversation.\", \"from\": 4100, \"to\": 4150, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4100, \"end\": 4109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ABC_Radio_Grandstand\", \"score\": 0.9981655931818795, \"rank\": 0.001837778050501459, \"text\": \"ABC Sport\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ABC_Radio_Grandstand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ABC_Radio_Grandstand\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We dive into the biggest story of the day and get you up to speed with everything else that's making headlines.\", \"from\": 4151, \"to\": 4262, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Emma McKeon only just claimed the crown as the Australian with the most gold medals, winning her sixth in the 4x100m relay on night one.\", \"from\": 4264, \"to\": 4400, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4264, \"end\": 4275, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_McKeon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emma McKeon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_McKeon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_McKeon\"}, {\"begin\": 4311, \"end\": 4321, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9999996381316778, \"rank\": 3.6024535303213817e-07, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McKeown now has two more individual events to go, the 200m backstroke in which she is the world record holder in both long and short-course pools.\", \"from\": 4402, \"to\": 4548, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Then there is the 200 IM and the small matter of the teenager who beat her to Commonwealth Games gold in the event, Summer McIntosh.\", \"from\": 4550, \"to\": 4682, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4628, \"end\": 4646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commonwealth_Games\", \"score\": 0.9998323240686046, \"rank\": 0.00016712694912051905, \"text\": \"Commonwealth Games\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commonwealth_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commonwealth_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 4666, \"end\": 4681, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Summer McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But McKeown is not the sort of swimmer to worry about things like that, the inner belief she has overrides any possible sense of cannot.\", \"from\": 4684, \"to\": 4820, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I just need to take it step by step,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 4822, \"to\": 4870, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The disappointment that McKeown had at missing her PB in Brisbane may have been a one such moment - she admitted then that the nerves were gnawing away at her.\", \"from\": 4872, \"to\": 5031, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4929, \"end\": 4937, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\", \"score\": 0.9999923444999872, \"rank\": 7.648507238762798e-06, \"text\": \"Brisbane\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But there has been enough evidence to suggest that this pool is not quite as quick as might have been expected - there have been no world records fall yet at this Games.\", \"from\": 5033, \"to\": 5202, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But disappointment is an alien feeling at La D\\u00e9fense Arena.\", \"from\": 5204, \"to\": 5263, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics is not about time.\", \"from\": 5265, \"to\": 5296, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Just timing.\", \"from\": 5297, \"to\": 5309, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And McKeown's timing is proving to be just about perfect.\", \"from\": 5311, \"to\": 5368, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Topic:Cricket  Topic:Cricket  Topic:Courts  Topic:NRL  Topic:NRL  Topic:Domestic Violence  Topic:Social Media  Topic:Federal Government  Topic:War  Topic:Royalty  Topic:Domestic Violence  Topic:Royalty  Topic:War  France  Olympic Games  Sport  Swimming  Topic:Domestic Violence  Topic:Social Media  Topic:Federal Government  Topic:War  Topic:Royalty  Topic:Rural and Remote Communities  Topic:Pollution  Topic:Geography  Topic:Royalty  We acknowledge Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples as the First Australians and Traditional Custodians of the lands where we live, learn, and work.\", \"from\": 5370, \"to\": 5963, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5420, \"end\": 5423, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rugby_League\", \"score\": 0.9998197449815436, \"rank\": 0.00018026639179689202, \"text\": \"NRL\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q10962\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rugby_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rugby_League\"}, {\"begin\": 5431, \"end\": 5434, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rugby_League\", \"score\": 0.9998197449815436, \"rank\": 0.00018026639179689202, \"text\": \"NRL\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q10962\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rugby_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rugby_League\"}, {\"begin\": 5584, \"end\": 5590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9455063803190082, \"rank\": 0.057179492972415424, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 5821, \"end\": 5831, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aboriginal_Australians\", \"score\": 0.6483826482933592, \"rank\": 0.5422990954775606, \"text\": \"Aboriginal\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aboriginal_Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aboriginal_Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 5908, \"end\": 5918, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hands_of_the_Cause\", \"score\": 0.8403979556800811, \"rank\": 0.18991246140118803, \"text\": \"Custodians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hands_of_the_Cause\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hands_of_the_Cause\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This service may include material from Agence France-Presse (AFP), APTN, Reuters, AAP, CNN and the BBC World Service which is copyright and cannot be reproduced.\", \"from\": 5965, \"to\": 6126, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6004, \"end\": 6024, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Agence France-Presse\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\"}, {\"begin\": 6032, \"end\": 6036, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aboriginal_Peoples_Television_Network\", \"score\": 0.9997704059078028, \"rank\": 0.00022964669994426145, \"text\": \"APTN\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aboriginal_Peoples_Television_Network\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aboriginal_Peoples_Television_Network\"}, {\"begin\": 6038, \"end\": 6045, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.298131299506442e-19, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 6052, \"end\": 6055, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.388024710056286e-14, \"text\": \"CNN\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\"}, {\"begin\": 6064, \"end\": 6081, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_World_Service\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.475259318205949e-15, \"text\": \"BBC World Service\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\", \"Q141683\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_World_Service\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_World_Service\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"AEST= Australian Eastern Standard Time which is 10 hours ahead of GMT (Greenwich Mean Time)\", \"from\": 6128, \"to\": 6219, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6128, \"end\": 6132, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Time_in_Australia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"AEST\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Time_in_Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Time_in_Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 6145, \"end\": 6161, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eastern_Time_Zone\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.475722724985974e-29, \"text\": \"Eastern Standard\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eastern_Time_Zone\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eastern_Time_Zone\"}, {\"begin\": 6194, \"end\": 6197, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greenwich_Mean_Time\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8148887442866317e-17, \"text\": \"GMT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greenwich_Mean_Time\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greenwich_Mean_Time\"}]}]}"